params.nonce: unique nonce used in proof to prevent replay
params.pubSignals: public signals expected by the verifier (must match prover) Expected `pubSignals` layout (example): pubSignals[0] = uint256(uint160(address(this)))      // wallet address pubSignals[1] = uint256(uint160(to))                 // recipient pubSignals[2] = amount                                // amount in wei pubSignals[3] = nonce                                 // nonce pubSignals[4] = uint256(ownerCommitment)             // owner commitment encoded as uint256 IMPORTANT: the prover must pack public inputs in exactly this order/encoding.
